# Branding rule (copy only — not visual design)

This rule governs **product-facing words** (nouns/labels tied to the vertical), not **look and feel**.

**Unrestricted (encourage creativity):** layout, spacing, grids, breakpoints, typography scale, color, borders, shadows, motion, imagery, icons, dark/light theme, component composition, new pages/sections, Tailwind/shadcn patterns — as long as payments/API contracts in [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md) and `.cursor/rules/payments.mdc` stay intact.

**In scope here:** user-visible **nouns** for the active vertical live in [`lib/branding.ts`](mdc:lib/branding.ts).
Pull them from there; do not hardcode "Restaurant", "Worker", "Tip", "Roosterwise",
or any other vertical-specific word in **interactive/product chrome** (see below).

```ts
import { branding } from '@/lib/branding';

// ✅
<h1>{branding.productName} console</h1>
<p>Manage your {branding.payeePlural.toLowerCase()}.</p>
<button>Run {branding.payoutNoun.toLowerCase()}</button>

// ❌
<h1>Roosterwise console</h1>
<p>Manage your workers.</p>
<button>Run tip-out</button>
```

## When you may keep a literal (copy freedom)

- Long-form **marketing** prose on the landing page (`app/page.tsx` hero, feature sections).
  Rewriting or extending marketing copy for a new vertical is encouraged.
- Illustrative examples in comments or docs.
- SVG monogram letters that follow `branding.productName.charAt(0)`.
- Dev-only values in `e2e-test.js`.

## When you must use `branding.*` (short UI chrome)

Use [`lib/branding.ts`](mdc:lib/branding.ts) for recurring **product nouns** in the app shell and flows:

- Form labels, table headers, page titles, breadcrumbs, primary buttons that name the product/payer/payee/payout.
- Toasts, error messages, success messages that reference those nouns.
- Email placeholder hints (`branding.payerSingular.toLowerCase()` works fine).

Do **not** interpret this rule as limiting CSS classes, component structure, or design refreshes — only avoid hardcoding **those nouns** outside `branding.ts` in chrome listed above.

## Reskinning checklist (one-file change)

When asked to "reskin to <vertical>":

1. Open `lib/branding.ts`.
2. Edit `productName`, `payerSingular/Plural`, `payeeSingular/Plural`,
   `payoutNoun/Plural`, `funderLabel`, `tagline`, `consoleHeading`,
   `consoleSubheading`.
3. Optional: update the marketing copy on `app/page.tsx`.
4. Stop. Do not edit `lib/types/*`, `lib/hooks/*`, `app/actions/*`, route
   handlers, or Redis keys.
